### GET all Inventories
GET http://localhost:5000/api/inventories

###

### GET Inventories for a specific Item by Item ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/inventories/item/1

###

### Create a new Inventory
POST http://localhost:5000/api/inventories
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "Id": 1,
    "ItemId": 2,
    "Description": "Sample Inventory",
    "ItemReference": "ITEM001",
    "LocationId": 1,
    "TotalOnHand": 100,
    "TotalExpected": 100,
    "TotalOrdered": 50,
    "TotalAllocated": 30,
    "TotalAvailable": 20
}

###

### Update an existing Inventory
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/inventories/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 1,
    "itemId": 1,
    "description": "Sample Inventory",
    "itemReference": "ITEM001",
    "locationId": 1,
    "totalOnHand": 150,
